Movies API (Current Scope)
Base URL: https://YOUR-RENDER-APP.onrender.com
Authentication: None
Content-Type: application/json
GET /moviebyyear
Returns all movies released in the specified year.

Query Parameters

year (required, integer, 4-digit)
Constraints: 1878–2100
Example: 1999
Success Response: 200 OK

Body:
success: boolean — Always true on success
message: string — Human-readable summary
data: object
year: number — The year queried
count: number — Number of movies returned
movies: array — List of movie records for the given year
id: number — Unique identifier
title: string — Movie title
year: number — Release year
Example:
{
"success": true,
"message": "Retrieved 2 movie(s) for year 1999",
"data": {
"year": 1999,
"count": 2,
"movies": [
{ "id": 42, "title": "The Matrix", "year": 1999 },
{ "id": 43, "title": "Fight Club", "year": 1999 }
]
}
}

Client Errors

400 Bad Request (missing or invalid year)

Body:
success: false
message: string — Explanation of what’s invalid
errorCode: string — One of: VALD_INVALID_FORMAT
Example:
{
"success": false,
"message": "Query parameter 'year' is required and must be a 4-digit number",
"errorCode": "VALD_INVALID_FORMAT"
}
404 Not Found (no movies for the year)

Body:
success: false
message: string — No results message
errorCode: string — One of: RSRC_NOT_FOUND
Example:
{
"success": false,
"message": "No movies found for year 1987",
"errorCode": "RSRC_NOT_FOUND"
}
Server Errors

500 Internal Server Error
Body:
success: false
message: string — Generic/internal error
errorCode: string — One of: SRVR_INTERNAL_ERROR or SRVR_DATABASE_ERROR
Example (database error):
{
"success": false,
"message": "Database error occurred",
"errorCode": "SRVR_DATABASE_ERROR"
}
Example Request

GET https://YOUR-RENDER-APP.onrender.com/moviebyyear?year=1999
Example cURL

curl -X GET "https://YOUR-RENDER-APP.onrender.com/moviebyyear?year=1999" -H "Accept: application/json"
